[h1]GK Raiding Expanded[/h1]

Capture pops. Strip planets. Wage wars the galaxy won't forget.

[h2]What's New[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]Pop capture on invasion[/b]: armies grab pops when they take a planet, not just during bombardment
[*] [b]Guaranteed capture on surrender[/b]: every enemy world pays its share when the war ends
[*] [b]Production-based pillaging[/b]: steal months of a planet's actual output in energy, minerals, alloys, and more
[*] [b]Pillage in any war[/b]: pillage-capable empires can strip hostile worlds in any conflict; [b]Pillage[/b] wars make those raids far richer
[*] [b]Raid exactly what you want[/b]: liberate slaves, skip robots, go robots-only, or take everything. War goals, policies, and civics let you tailor every raid
[*] [b]Raiding wars only[/b]: no free pop abduction during conquest or subjugation
[/list]

[h2]Pillaging[/h2]
[list]
[*] Loot scales with what the planet actually produces: energy, minerals, food, alloys, consumer goods, strategic resources, and more
[*] Research and Unity convert to Consumer Goods as war plunder; Trade value is doubled
[*] Worlds yield plunder as they are battered down by fleets and armies
[*] Pillage-capable empires can keep extracting tribute in any war; [b]Pillage[/b] wars rip far richer tribute out of the same worlds
[*] Less-ravaged colonies still have more to give when they are invaded or forced to surrender
[*] Surviving colonies that still had wealth to give can be left paying tribute after surrender
[*] Pillage Efficiency modifier allows scaling yields through traditions or other sources
[/list]

[h2]Balanced Raiding & Reaping[/h2]

Raids are rebalanced around percentage-based caps: smaller, less devastating, and multiplayer-friendly. Raided empires get workforce and growth bonuses to bounce back.

Want the old unlimited raiding? Declare a [b]Reaping[/b] war: capture every pop on every world. But the galaxy doesn't forgive Reapers: massive opinion penalties (up to -200), with Egalitarians and Xenophiles reacting most harshly. Per-pop opinion tracking means the more you reap, the more you're hated.

[h2]War Goals[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]Raiding[/b]: Capture pops (up to 10% on surrender, 20% during war) and lead a side that can also strip tribute from enemy worlds
[*] [b]Pillage[/b]: Pure resource extraction with much richer tribute. No pop capture
[*] [b]Emancipation[/b]: Liberate enslaved pops only. No resource pillaging
[*] [b]Robo-Liberation[/b]: Free robotic pops only. No resource pillaging
[*] [b]Reaping[/b]: Unlimited pop capture across all enemy worlds. Extreme opinion penalties
[/list]

[h2]Civics[/h2]

[b]Emancipators / Liberation Enterprise[/b] (Standard / Megacorp)
[i]Egalitarian + Militarist[/i]
Unlocks the Emancipation war goal to liberate enslaved pops. Grants +50% Army Morale, +50% Raiding Capacity.
Councilor: Liberation Commander: +2% Ship Fire Rate per level.

[b]Robo-Liberators / Synthetic Liberation Corp[/b] (Standard / Megacorp)
[i]Materialist[/i]
Unlocks the Robo-Liberation war goal to free robotic pops. Grants +50% Raiding Capacity.
Councilor: Synthetic Rights Advocate: -2% Robot Upkeep and +1% Robot Happiness per level.

[b]Harvest Incorporated[/b] (Megacorp)
[i]Militarist[/i]
A corporate population harvester. -20% Slave Market Cost, +10% Slave Workforce.
Councilor: Acquisitions Director: -4% Slave Market Cost and -2% Slave Upkeep per level.

[b]Harvesting Protocol[/b] (Machine Intelligence)
Starts with Grid Amalgamated organic battery pops. +1 Energy and +1 Unity from batteries, +25% Legion Node XP.

[b]Freedom Directive[/b] (Machine Intelligence)
Machine robo-liberators. -15% Robot Upkeep, +10% Pop Assembly, +50% Raiding Capacity, +25% Legion Node XP.

[h2]Policies[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]Raiding Focus[/b]: Choose between Plunder, Despoliation (no pop capture), Emancipation, or Robo-Liberation
[*] [b]Robot Raiding[/b]: Capture Robots, Organics Only, or Robots Only
[/list]
